Apparently, the added &quot;TH&quot; was their way of celebrating the assembly of the final (99th) Hawk 81A-2; it was not a reference to a unit number, since the AVG had only three squadrons - 1st &quot;Adam &amp; Eves,&quot; 2nd &quot;Panda Bears&quot; &amp; 3rd &quot;Hell's Angels.&quot;

This aircraft was later re-numbered &quot;92&quot;, assigned to the AVG's 3rd Pursuit Squadron with pilot Robert &quot;Duke&quot; Hedman.

Pentecost's name doesn't appear on the AVG's roster; perhaps he worked for CAMCO (Central Aircraft Manufacturing Company), the concern tasked with assembling the birds - and doing subsequent major repair work.
